cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DS, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the evaluation of synthetic social contact networks. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it involves the study of human populations and their interactions. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) as it involves the integration of data from various sources. The use of multiple measures of graph complexity suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the study of human activity and interaction could place it under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
